1
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:05,960
I don't want to be alone.

2
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:08,600
Can I come to you?

3
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:29,080
Are you there yet?

4
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,320
I have an impromptu meeting.

5
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:31,880
Go to my office and wait for me.

6
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:18,780
Li Xingyao.

7
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:22,340
It really is you.

8
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:23,580
Why are you here?

9
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:24,820
Back to work.

10
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:26,740
Good that you're back.

11
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,900
Since you want to suck up to Teacher Zhou,

12
00:02:29,140 --> 00:02:31,380
you need to be close to the source.

13
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:32,940
Gain more visibility, right?

14
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:35,420
Stop pretending.

15
00:02:35,740 --> 00:02:38,100
Everyone knows you're Teacher Zhou's chosen one.

16
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:39,300
Not bad, you.

17
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,500
Able to win over Teacher Zhou.

18
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:42,820
Teacher Xingyao, from now on I'll follow you.

19
00:02:43,220 --> 00:02:43,780
Let's go.

20
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:50,300
Thanks to our big star, Teacher Wei Tiantian.

21
00:02:51,820 --> 00:02:54,300
Alright then, I'll wait for your news.

22
00:02:55,580 --> 00:02:56,820
Also thank you very much for coming this time

23
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:58,060
to be a judge for our new talent program.

24
00:02:58,580 --> 00:02:59,220
You're welcome.

25
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:00,380
The main thing is,

26
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,940
I'm also curious about how good

27
00:03:02,940 --> 00:03:03,900
The person our Teacher Zhou has chosen really is.

28
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:05,060
I'm off.

29
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:10,220
So, want to grab a meal together?

30
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:11,100
You go ahead.

31
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:12,020
I still have things to deal with.

32
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,220
But you know,

33
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:28,980
last time you couldn't sing in front of us.

34
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:31,500
Can you perform on stage in front of

35
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,300
The judging panel and the audience?

36
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,220
Li Xingyao, can you do it?

37
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:39,020
Maybe he just didn't want to sing for us.

38
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:41,420
He's probably already sung for Teacher Zhou.

39
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:42,860
That's true.

40
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,020
What's the benefit of singing for us?

41
00:03:45,020 --> 00:03:45,700
Just as expected.

42
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:47,500
The so-called social anxiety

43
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:49,300
depends on who it's with.

44
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:51,660
Teacher Xingyao.

45
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:53,140
Say something, Teacher Xingyao.

46
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:55,020
Why isn't Teacher Xingyao speaking?

47
00:03:55,020 --> 00:03:55,740
Teacher Xingyao.

48
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:58,980
Teacher Xingyao.

49
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:00,740
From now on, I'll follow you.

50
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:04,700
Come, Teacher Xingyao, sit down.

51
00:04:07,540 --> 00:04:08,420
Teacher Xingyao,

52
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:10,100
I'll also rely on you from now on.

53
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:16,660
These are the archived materials from last year's music festival.

54
00:04:20,180 --> 00:04:20,780
Organize them, will you?

55
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:21,900
not

56
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:23,300
Why?

57
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:25,580
A few of these might be

58
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:27,300
your opponents in the internal selection this year.

59
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:28,540
I also hope you can

60
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:30,180
get to know this year's pop styles in advance.

61
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:31,820
I'm helping you so much.

62
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:33,180
You wouldn't be ungrateful, would you?

63
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:35,220
Thank you.

64
00:04:58,220 --> 00:04:58,700
Xiao Yao.

65
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:00,020
Xiao Yao.

66
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:03,460
Come.

67
00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:09,180
What's going on here?

68
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:13,980
Li Xingyao,

69
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,060
why are you here?

70
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,420
Didn't you resign?

71
00:05:16,940 --> 00:05:17,780
I want to ask,

72
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:21,100
why is the guest I invited working here?

73
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:22,900
I don't know.

74
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,180
The music festival archiving project —

75
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:28,780
who is responsible for it?

76
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:33,900
Do I need to ask again?

77
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,380
It's... it's me, Teacher Zhou.

78
00:05:37,660 --> 00:05:40,620
I didn't know he was a guest you invited.

79
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,140
Process his resignation now.

80
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:43,180
Teacher Zhou,

81
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:44,300
it might be a misunderstanding.

82
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:46,780
Wang Rui usually doesn't cause any trouble.

83
00:05:46,940 --> 00:05:48,140
Let him leave today.

84
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:49,860
This...

85
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:52,700
Let's go.

86
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:54,500
Go.

87
00:05:59,340 --> 00:06:00,140
Pack up.

88
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,520
I'm sorry.

89
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:09,240
What?

90
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,320
It seems I've caused you trouble again.

91
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,320
Were you wrong?

92
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,640
I will not allow

93
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,600
any bullying among colleagues in my company.

94
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,560
Even if it weren't you,

95
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,800
but precisely because it is you,

96
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,480
it actually saved me a lot of time in making a decision.

97
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,880
Because based on my understanding of you,

98
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,320
you wouldn't actively provoke anyone.

99
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:36,400
Isn't that right?

100
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:38,960
But if

101
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,200
I hadn't come today,

102
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,840
He wouldn't have been fired either.

103
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:45,600
Xiao Yao,

104
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,640
you don't need to sympathize with those who are unkind to you,

105
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,560
nor feel guilty for their misfortune.

106
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,480
Because what they are experiencing now

107
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,200
is caused by themselves.

108
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,000
They brought it upon themselves.

109
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,280
It has nothing to do with you.

110
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,280
You don't have to take responsibility for it.

111
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,600
Your kindness

112
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,360
should not be wasted on those who are not worth it.

113
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,600
Eat something quickly.

114
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,960
You haven't eaten all day yesterday.

115
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,280
Are you blind?

116
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,360
Xu Xiujie.

117
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,120
What?

118
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,600
Don't recognize me?

119
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,600
Brother Qiang.

120
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,400
He's a big internet celebrity now,

121
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,480
a food review blogger.

122
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,680
Living the good life.

123
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,520
How could he still remember us old classmates?

124
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,440
He's all dressed up.

125
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,000
What about your

126
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,400
mute little sidekick Li Xingyao?

127
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,480
Aren't you two the best of friends?

128
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,280
I kind of miss him.

129
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:46,400
This kid has such delicate skin.

130
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,760
When he cries,

131
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,000
it's really something.

132
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:49,760
Shut up.

133
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,680
Oh, dear!

134
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,360
Still protecting him?

135
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,360
Tell me the truth:

136
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,960
Have you two slept together?

137
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,560
Keep your mouth clean.

138
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:00,600
What?

139
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,760
Look down on you,

140
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,800
or have you found a better prospect?

141
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:06,800
No wonder.

142
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:10,840
Back then you were just a dog by Li Xingyao's side.

143
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,720
He wouldn't even spare you an extra glance.

144
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,800
The more I talk, the more I miss him.

145
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,520
What's Li Xingyao's phone number?

146
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,120
I need to catch up with him.

147
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,080
Right now, he

148
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,280
is a signed singer of a gold medal producer,

149
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,560
a rising star.

150
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:32,480
What about you?

151
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:34,520
Besides barking in front of me,

152
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,240
what else can you do?

153
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,960
You will always be scum, trash.

154
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,360
This is the stage where you will perform.

155
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,680
Xiao Yao,

156
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,200
do you want to come up and feel it?

157
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,360
Are you so bothered by touching me?

158
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:30,960
No.

159
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,360
I'm not bothered.

160
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:37,560
I'm afraid.

161
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,520
Alright.

162
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:44,640
I understand.

163
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:01,840
Xiao Yao.

164
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,080
Good night.

165
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:40,880
Next: Li Xingyao.

166
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:56,960
You may begin.

167
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:48,720
What's going on?

168
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,520
Why did it stop?

169
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,480
Why is it stuck?

170
00:14:58,800 --> 00:14:59,680
Forgot the lyrics, obviously.

171
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,880
This contestant doesn't have the mental strength.

172
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:04,200
Why is he wearing a mask?

173
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,480
Is he lip-syncing?

174
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:07,560
Sing!

175
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:08,640
Just leave, leave!

176
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,480
I guess he wants to sing, but he can't

177
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,880
Wasting everyone's time.

178
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:16,760
Get off, get off, get off!

179
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,800
Sing! Don't you love to sing?

180
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:20,960
Why aren't you singing?

181
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,240
Sing two lines for me.

182
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:30,880
Get off!

183
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:31,880
Just leave, leave!

184
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:32,720
Go!

185
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:39,640
Finally left

186
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:41,480
Next.

187
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,080
That Li Xingyao you recommended —

188
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,000
what exactly happened?

189
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,040
Why did he run off?

190
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,160
We'll talk about it later.

191
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:09,220
Hello

192
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:11,160
Do you know where he is?

193
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,080
So what if I do?

194
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:14,560
Why should I tell you?

195
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,280
Because I know better than you how to comfort him.

196
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,000
Is that enough?

197
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:21,280
Fine.

198
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,640
And coincidentally, there are some things

199
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,800
I want to ask you face to face.

200
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,080
I still can't sing.

201
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,480
Back then I boasted to you,

202
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:57,720
but I still couldn't do it.

203
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,840
You must think I'm ridiculous, right?

204
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,400
Xingyao,

205
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:06,520
how could I possibly think you're ridiculous?

206
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:08,600
You already stood up there.

207
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:10,800
You were already very brave.

208
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,880
Things that others can do easily,

209
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:17,960
I have to work very hard

210
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,840
to achieve just a little bit.

211
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:22,920
Someone like me,

212
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,280
still deluding myself into being a glimmer of light for others —

213
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,760
I'm truly too ridiculous.

214
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:32,760
It's all because of Wang Daqiang and those bastards.

215
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:33,640
How could you —

216
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,800
Does he always drink like this?

217
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,320
Don't you know him very well?

218
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,480
Why ask me?

219
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,080
I remember last time we met,

220
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,160
we talked quite politely.

221
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:21,880
That was because

222
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,040
I thought you were just his boss,

223
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,720
his talent scout.

224
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,320
I didn't expect

225
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,120
you had ulterior motives.

226
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:32,080
If you have something to say, just say it directly.

227
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:33,160
Fine.

228
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,120
You deliberately approached me,

229
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,800
learned about Xingyao's past,

230
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,280
investigated our relationship.

231
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,840
Zhou Jing'an,

232
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,040
you just want to take Xingyao away from me.

233
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:46,720
I don't deny that.

234
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,360
What are you so proud of?

235
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:50,840
It's because

236
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,600
what I couldn't achieve after more than ten years of effort,

237
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:55,240
you achieved effortlessly.

238
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,200
So you think you've won,

239
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:58,480
don't you?

240
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,480
Isn't that so?

241
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:03,920
Do you know where you lost?

242
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,040
Because you want his change

243
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,040
to be into the version you want.

244
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,880
The redemption you give him

245
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:12,680
is also what you think he needs.

246
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,000
But Xiao Yao doesn't need anyone's redemption at all.

247
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:19,600
What he needs

248
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,720
is a stable pivot point.

249
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:23,560
You can't provide it,

250
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,200
but I can.

251
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,840
Xingyao and I have depended on each other for more than ten years.

252
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,960
I am the person in this world who knows him best,

253
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:37,920
who understands him best.

254
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:40,600
What qualifications do you have to say these things in front of me?

255
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:44,800
Perhaps it was you before I appeared.

256
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,000
Thank you for taking care of him all these years.

257
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:49,400
From now on,

258
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,680
I will be responsible for everything about him.

259
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,720
I like Xingyao.

260
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,480
I am willing to take care of him.

261
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:57,080
And what gives you the right —

262
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,080
I —

263
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:02,960
You —

264
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,760
are just an old friend he hasn't seen for many years.

265
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,200
What's between us two

266
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:10,880
doesn't need your thanks.

267
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:13,760
Let's go, Xingyao.

268
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,320
Going home.

269
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:20,560
I can do it myself.

270
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:21,600
Come on.

271
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,080
I said I can do it myself.

272
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,760
He will stay at my place for the next few days.

273
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:39,140
Before he steps back onto the stage,

274
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,040
I will not allow anyone

275
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,640
or anything to disturb him.

276
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,360
I can do it myself.

277
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,400
Li Xingyao,

278
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:46,880
let me ask you.

279
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,680
Why did you push me away today?

280
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:54,200
You are the one who pushed away.

281
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,640
Why are you blaming me?

282
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,080
So you left with him.

283
00:22:59,280 --> 00:22:59,880
Yes.

284
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,200
You like him.

285
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,560
No.

286
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,000
Then why do you let him touch you,

287
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:06,840
but not me?

288
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:08,680
It's different.

289
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,640
What's different?

290
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:13,920
Speak.

291
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:17,720
Because only when you are in front of me

292
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,280
do I want —

293
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:21,480
Want what?

294
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,840
Want more.

295
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:35,960
Maybe he

296
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:38,740
does like me after all.
